<subSubSection lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="418" pageId="1" pageNumber="417" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1633,2020]" pageId="1" pageNumber="417">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,1813,1839]" pageId="1" pageNumber="417">Remarks</emphasis>
. Species for 
<collectingCountry box="[453,540,1813,1839]" name="Uganda" pageId="1" pageNumber="417">Uganda</collectingCountry>
for the first time was recorded by 
<bibRefCitation author="Kiriakoff, S. G." box="[925,1156,1813,1840]" pageId="1" pageNumber="417" refId="ref7473" refString="Kiriakoff, S. G. (1958) Ruwenzori Expedition, 1952. Vol. I. 2 - 3. Trustees of the British Museum, London, 53 pp." type="book" year="1958">Kiriakoff (1958: 16)</bibRefCitation>
. It was found at Kilembe and Fort Portal, and reported in combination with Phryganopsis 
<bibRefCitation author="Felder, R." box="[882,1027,1849,1875]" pageId="1" pageNumber="417" pagination="75 - 107" refId="ref7160" refString="Felder, R. (1874) Lepidoptera. In: Felder, C., Felder, R. &amp; Rogenhofer, A. F. (Eds.), Reise der osterreichischen Fregatte Novara um die Erde, Vienna, Zoology, 2 (Abt. 2), pls. 75 - 120 (1874), Erklarung to 75 - 107 (1875)." type="book chapter" year="1874">Felder, 1874</bibRefCitation>
. This species has also recently been recorded for the 
<collectingCountry box="[337,556,1885,1911]" name="Guinea-Bissau" pageId="1" pageNumber="417">Republic of Guinea</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Durante, M. A. &amp; Panzera, S." box="[570,863,1885,1912]" pageId="1" pageNumber="417" pagination="88 - 90" refId="ref7031" refString="Durante, M. A. &amp; Panzera, S. (2002 a) Pusiola unipunctana maior n. ssp. della Repubblica di Guinea (Lepidoptera, Arctiidae, Lithosiinae). Lambillionea, 102 (1), 88 - 90." type="journal article" year="2002">Durante &amp; Panzera 2002a</bibRefCitation>
) and 
<collectingCountry box="[925,998,1886,1912]" name="Kenya" pageId="1" pageNumber="417">Kenya</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Kuhne, L." box="[1013,1156,1885,1911]" pageId="1" pageNumber="417" pagination="157 - 168" refId="ref7684" refString="Kuhne, L. (2008) Subfamily Lithosiinae, footman moth or lichens-bears (Noctuoidea, Arctiidae). In: Kuhne, L. (Ed.), Butterflies and moth diversity of the Kakamega forest (Kenya). Published by the author, London, pp. 157 - 168." type="book chapter" year="2008">Kühne 2008</bibRefCitation>
), having previously been recorded for 
<collectingCountry box="[294,440,1921,1948]" name="Sierra Leone" pageId="1" pageNumber="417">Sierra Leone</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[450,526,1921,1947]" name="Ghana" pageId="1" pageNumber="417">Ghana</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[537,624,1921,1947]" name="Nigeria" pageId="1" pageNumber="417">Nigeria</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[634,754,1921,1947]" name="Cameroon" pageId="1" pageNumber="417">Cameroon</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[764,970,1921,1947]" name="Equatorial Guinea" pageId="1" pageNumber="417">Equatorial Guinea</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[981,1331,1921,1947]" name="Democratic Republic of the Congo" pageId="1" pageNumber="417">Democratic Republic of Congo</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1342,1432,1921,1947]" name="Uganda" pageId="1" pageNumber="417">Uganda</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[151,233,1957,1983]" name="Angola" pageId="1" pageNumber="417">Angola</collectingCountry>
(see 
<bibRefCitation author="De Prins, J. &amp; De Prins, W." box="[290,576,1957,1984]" pageId="1" pageNumber="417" refId="ref6502" refString="De Prins, J. &amp; De Prins, W. (2011 - 2021) Afromoths, online database of Afrotropical moth species (Lepidoptera). Available from: http: // www. afromoths. net (accessed 7 September 2021)" type="url" year="2011">De Prins &amp; De Prins 2011</bibRefCitation>
–2021 for detailed bibliography). For the subspecies distribution records from the 
<collectingCountry box="[192,415,1993,2019]" name="Guinea-Bissau" pageId="1" pageNumber="417">Republic of Guinea</collectingCountry>
, please refer to the Discussion.
</paragraph>
